-- MOVES-AmEx appoints Neal Sample as president, enterprise growth
-- 
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 07:57AM EDT
-- None



Sept 30 (Reuters) - New York-based financial services provider American Express Co <AXP.N> appointed Neal Sample as president, enterprise growth, effective immediately.

The company said Sample would replace Dan Schulman, who left to join Ebay Inc <EBAY.O> as chief executive of its PayPal business which plans on going public. [ID:nBw1p77dNa] Sample will report to Chief Executive Kenneth Chenault, AmEx said.